<h2>Finding 6: AI Overviews Reduce Top-Ranked CTR by Up to 60%</h2>
<p><strong>Background:</strong> SEMrush and Ahrefs independently tracked AI Overview appearance rates and click-through rate impacts across 500,000 keywords in Q1 2026.</p>
<p><strong>Results:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>AI Overviews appear on 25.8% of Google searches (up from 15% in mid-2025)</li>
<li>When AI Overviews appear for a query, CTR for the #1 organic result drops 15-60% depending on query type</li>
<li>Informational queries see the largest CTR reduction (up to 60%)</li>
<li>Commercial queries see smaller reductions (15-25%)</li>
<li>Local queries are least affected (5-10% CTR change)</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>What this means:</strong> AI Overviews are not killing SEO. They are changing which queries are valuable to target. Informational queries that AI can answer directly are becoming less valuable for traffic. Commercial, local, and complex queries that require human judgment remain strong. The strategy shift is clear: target queries where AI cannot fully satisfy the user.</p>
